# Azure App Service Deployment Configuration

## Deployment Steps (will be automated in setup guide)

1. Create App Service Plan
2. Create Web App
3. Configure environment variables
4. Deploy code
5. Test endpoint

## Required Azure Resources

- Resource Group: bug-position-bot-rg
- App Service Plan: bug-bot-plan (Free F1 tier)
- Web App: bug-position-bot-{unique-id}

## Environment Variables to Configure in Azure

All variables from .env file must be added to Azure App Service Configuration:
- ADO_ORGANIZATION_URL
- ADO_PROJECT_NAME
- ADO_PAT
- MICROSOFT_APP_ID
- MICROSOFT_APP_PASSWORD

## Startup Command

gunicorn --bind=0.0.0.0:8000 --worker-class aiohttp.GunicornWebWorker execution.teams_bug_bot:app

Note: Will need to install gunicorn for production deployment
